Doe you not read in the Acts of the Apostles, what labour and suffering they underwent to bring people out of carnall rudiments and ordinances of men, and to bring them to the worship in spirit and truth alone, both as to time, place, and order; how did they run in hazard of their lives, into Temples, Synagogues, and set places of worship, to bring them out of Temples made with hands, to worship where the Spirit should lead them, without respect of places; that so the words of the Lord Iesus might be fulfilled, who had said, Not in the Temple, nor in the mountaine,
John 4.21, 24. Acts 7.48. Acts 17.24. but in spirit and in truth should the Father be worshipped; and did not Stephen lose his life for telling them that God that made the world dwelt not in Temples made with hands;
